reviewText: It is really refreshing to see a family movie like this one come along-there are so few of them out there these days! This tells the story of a young boy,Tommy,who must become a man after his dad goes off to war and never returns. He and his family face the prospect of losing their farm,thanks to a greedy land developer named Dodge Davis(played superbly by Kevin Sorbo). Then along comes Jackie A,a feisty mule with an attitude-and oh,he can talk. After being bullied by the other boys in his neighborhood,Tommy decides to enter Jackie A in the local stock show competition in hopes of winning enough money to save the farm. This is one of those feel good movies that the whole family will enjoy despite the PG rating.
Loved the humor in this film, especially the mule's name.
A feel good movie. I enjoyed it. Thank you.
